[The FMD outbreak in the Indian state Karnataka (map at http://tinyurl.com/kk2zuux) has been spreading at least since mid-September 2013, accompanied by political struggles and media hype. The numbers of affected farms, sick animals and mortalities were varying, probably biased due to political considerations. However, the epizootic seems indeed to be of significant dimensions.

FMD is endemic in India; the virus serotypes circulating during 2012 were O, Asia1 and A. Until the mid-90s, serotype C was recorded as well (see WRLFMD India page at http://www.wrlfmd.org/fmd_genotyping/asia/ind.htm).

Further to a previous, now repeated request for information on the serotype of the involved FMD virus, we would appreciate details, if available, on its genotyping results and of the virus strains included in the applied vaccine. - Mod.AS]
